{"parentUuid":null,"isSidechain":true,"promptId":"dcbe4efb-6e32-4db6-a75a-aa49b911d737","agentId":"a2c2fb2f89230a0db","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":"Use WebSearch and WebFetch to research the CONCRETE RESULTS on ALGORITHMS AND MATHEMATICS achieved by Google DeepMind's AlphaEvolve (2025). I need specific numbers with exact source URLs.\n\nFocus on these specific claims and verify exact figures:\n- 4x4 complex-valued matrix multiplication using 48 scalar multiplications (vs Strassen's 49), the first improvement in 56 years over Strassen's 1969 algorithm\n- Advances on open math problems: applied to ~50 open problems in mathematics/analysis/geometry/combinatorics; rediscovered state-of-the-art in ~75% and improved on ~20%\n- The kissing number problem in 11 dimensions (new lower bound — find the exact number, e.g. 593)\n- Any other math results (e.g. Erdos minimum overlap, uncertainty principles, sum-difference sets)\n\nPrefer primary sources: deepmind.google blog post (\"AlphaEvolve a Gemini-powered coding agent for designing advanced algorithms\"), the arxiv white paper PDF (arxiv 2506.13131 or the DeepMind white paper). Cross-check numbers across sources.\n\nReturn a list of falsifiable, specific claims with exact numbers. Each claim MUST have its exact source URL. Do not write files — return findings as your final text message."},"uuid":"f4e9ea49-dab4-48b9-bee0-982993ef0eb2","timestamp":"2026-06-21T07:34:40.215Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/gg/Work/Yogi","sessionId":"d8d6b712-ec33-4776-a194-d9a72216a25f","version":"2.1.183","gitBranch":"main","slug":"bright-wondering-lantern"}
