{"parentUuid":"cd33fd09-8586-442e-9ee1-a0c6d37b5940","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a2c2fb2f89230a0db","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_01VHz4YEgnzwmDXEevt1ncNT","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_016F8JFpFhKouaboUC16t6ak","name":"WebSearch","input":{"query":"AlphaEvolve kissing number 11 dimensions 593 new lower bound DeepMind 2025"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1003,"cache_creation_input_tokens":5855,"cache_read_input_tokens":6425,"output_tokens":390,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":5855},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":1003,"output_tokens":390,"cache_read_input_tokens":6425,"cache_creation_input_tokens":5855,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":5855,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":{"cache_miss_reason":{"type":"tools_changed","cache_missed_input_tokens":8187}}},"requestId":"req_011CcG23u9Ev6GC6Qa7e2RiJ","attributionAgent":"general-purpose","attributionSkill":"deep-research","type":"assistant","uuid":"fc0a03f2-a93f-4dce-905a-27bb72a090a2","timestamp":"2026-06-21T07:34:48.545Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/gg/Work/Yogi","sessionId":"d8d6b712-ec33-4776-a194-d9a72216a25f","version":"2.1.183","gitBranch":"main","slug":"bright-wondering-lantern"}
{"parentUuid":"cd33fd09-8586-442e-9ee1-a0c6d37b5940","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"dcbe4efb-6e32-4db6-a75a-aa49b911d737","agentId":"a2c2fb2f89230a0db","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_011CuQhXwX14WeHQnpzMSymp","type":"tool_result","content":"# AlphaEvolve Mathematical and Algorithm Results\n\n## Matrix Multiplication (4x4 Complex-Valued Matrices)\n\n**Key Finding:** AlphaEvolve discovered an algorithm using 48 scalar multiplications, improving upon Strassen's 1969 algorithm.\n\n**Exact Quote:** \"AlphaEvolve's procedure found an algorithm to multiply 4x4 complex-valued matrices using 48 scalar multiplications, improving upon Strassen's 1969 algorithm that was previously known as the best in this setting.\"\n\n**Note:** The content does not specify Strassen's exact number for this case or mention a \"56 years\" claim.\n\n## Open Mathematical Problems\n\n**Scope:** The system addressed over 50 open problems across multiple domains.\n\n**Results:**\n- **~75% rediscovered** state-of-the-art solutions\n- **~20% improved** previously best known solutions\n\n**Exact Quote:** \"In roughly 75% of cases, it rediscovered state-of-the-art solutions, to the best of our knowledge. And in 20% of cases, AlphaEvolve improved the previously best known solutions.\"\n\n## Kissing Number Problem (11 Dimensions)\n\n**Achievement:** AlphaEvolve discovered a configuration establishing a new lower bound.\n\n**Exact Quote:** \"AlphaEvolve discovered a configuration of 593 outer spheres and established a new lower bound in 11 dimensions.\"\n\n## Other Problems Mentioned\n\nThe webpage does not provide specific numerical results for Erdős minimum overlap, uncertainty principles, sum-difference sets, or matrix multiplication tensor decompositions beyond the 4x4 case noted above."}]},"uuid":"1eac6048-6818-43b2-8830-2f82d2f0cab2","timestamp":"2026-06-21T07:34:55.394Z","toolUseResult":{"bytes":151623,"code":200,"codeText":"OK","result":"# AlphaEvolve Mathematical and Algorithm Results\n\n## Matrix Multiplication (4x4 Complex-Valued Matrices)\n\n**Key Finding:** AlphaEvolve discovered an algorithm using 48 scalar multiplications, improving upon Strassen's 1969 algorithm.\n\n**Exact Quote:** \"AlphaEvolve's procedure found an algorithm to multiply 4x4 complex-valued matrices using 48 scalar multiplications, improving upon Strassen's 1969 algorithm that was previously known as the best in this setting.\"\n\n**Note:** The content does not specify Strassen's exact number for this case or mention a \"56 years\" claim.\n\n## Open Mathematical Problems\n\n**Scope:** The system addressed over 50 open problems across multiple domains.\n\n**Results:**\n- **~75% rediscovered** state-of-the-art solutions\n- **~20% improved** previously best known solutions\n\n**Exact Quote:** \"In roughly 75% of cases, it rediscovered state-of-the-art solutions, to the best of our knowledge. And in 20% of cases, AlphaEvolve improved the previously best known solutions.\"\n\n## Kissing Number Problem (11 Dimensions)\n\n**Achievement:** AlphaEvolve discovered a configuration establishing a new lower bound.\n\n**Exact Quote:** \"AlphaEvolve discovered a configuration of 593 outer spheres and established a new lower bound in 11 dimensions.\"\n\n## Other Problems Mentioned\n\nThe webpage does not provide specific numerical results for Erdős minimum overlap, uncertainty principles, sum-difference sets, or matrix multiplication tensor decompositions beyond the 4x4 case noted above.","durationMs":6701,"url":"https://deepmind.google/discover/blog/alphaevolve-a-gemini-powered-coding-agent-for-designing-advanced-algorithms/"},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"cd33fd09-8586-442e-9ee1-a0c6d37b5940","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/gg/Work/Yogi","sessionId":"d8d6b712-ec33-4776-a194-d9a72216a25f","version":"2.1.183","gitBranch":"main","slug":"bright-wondering-lantern"}
{"parentUuid":"fc0a03f2-a93f-4dce-905a-27bb72a090a2","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"dcbe4efb-6e32-4db6-a75a-aa49b911d737","agentId":"a2c2fb2f89230a0db","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_016F8JFpFhKouaboUC16t6ak","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"AlphaEvolve kissing number 11 dimensions 593 new lower bound DeepMind 2025\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Google DeepMind's AlphaEvolve: A Breakthrough in AI-Driven Scientific Discovery\",\"url\":\"https://theoutpost.ai/news-story/google-deep-mind-s-alpha-evolve-a-breakthrough-in-ai-driven-algorithm-discovery-15378/\"},{\"title\":\"AlphaEvolve Tackles Kissing Problem & More - IEEE Spectrum\",\"url\":\"https://spectrum.ieee.org/deepmind-alphaevolve\"},{\"title\":\"AlphaEvolve - AI Powered Coding Agent For Designing Algorithms\",\"url\":\"https://alphaevolveai.dev/\"},{\"title\":\"AlphaEvolve: A coding agent for scientific and algorithmic discovery\",\"url\":\"https://storage.googleapis.com/deepmind-media/DeepMind.com/Blog/alphaevolve-a-gemini-powered-coding-agent-for-designing-advanced-algorithms/AlphaEvolve.pdf\"},{\"title\":\"AlphaEvolve: A Gemini-powered coding agent for designing advanced algorithms — Google DeepMind\",\"url\":\"https://deepmind.google/blog/alphaevolve-a-gemini-powered-coding-agent-for-designing-advanced-algorithms/\"},{\"title\":\"Meet AlphaEvolve, the Google AI that writes its own code—and just saved millions in computing costs | VentureBeat\",\"url\":\"https://venturebeat.com/ai/meet-alphaevolve-the-google-ai-that-writes-its-own-code-and-just-saved-millions-in-computing-costs\"},{\"title\":\"5 impressive feats of DeepMind’s new self-evolving AI coding agent\",\"url\":\"https://thenextweb.com/news/5-feats-of-deepmind-ai-coding-agent-alphaevolve\"},{\"title\":\"Google DeepMind Unveils AlphaEvolve: An AI Coding Agent for Research & EdTech - Elets digitalLEARNING - Elets Digital Learning\",\"url\":\"https://digitallearning.eletsonline.com/2025/05/google-deepmind-unveils-alphaevolve-an-ai-coding-agent-for-research-edtech/\"},{\"title\":\"AlphaEvolve: The AI That Just Rewrote the Rules of Math, Code, and Discovery | by Subinkrishnan | Medium\",\"url\":\"https://medium.com/@subinkrishnan/alphaevolve-the-ai-that-just-rewrote-the-rules-of-math-code-and-discovery-046373410aa4\"},{\"title\":\"Mathematical exploration and discovery at scale\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2511.02864\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, I found comprehensive information about your query:\n\nAlphaEvolve, an AI agent developed by Google DeepMind, has increased the lower bound on the kissing number in 11 dimensions from 592 to 593.\n\nThe kissing number problem is a geometric challenge that has fascinated mathematicians for over 300 years and concerns the maximum number of non-overlapping spheres that touch a common unit sphere. AlphaEvolve discovered a configuration of 593 outer spheres and established a new lower bound in 11 dimensions.\n\nWhen applied to over 50 open problems in mathematics, AlphaEvolve improved on the best-known solutions in 20% of cases. AlphaEvolve integrates DeepMind's Gemini family of large language models with an evolutionary algorithmic framework, enabling it to propose numerous candidate solutions, evaluate their effectiveness using automated metrics, and iteratively refine them to discover more efficient and novel algorithms.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"1af008c7-3863-45d3-97bf-3d793c559cc9","timestamp":"2026-06-21T07:34:55.888Z","toolUseResult":{"query":"AlphaEvolve kissing number 11 dimensions 593 new lower bound DeepMind 2025","results":[{"tool_use_id":"srvtoolu_01HihiRRDEU9wkf5YTeEsvXY","content":[{"title":"Google DeepMind's AlphaEvolve: A Breakthrough in AI-Driven Scientific Discovery","url":"https://theoutpost.ai/news-story/google-deep-mind-s-alpha-evolve-a-breakthrough-in-ai-driven-algorithm-discovery-15378/"}